25|$|The {{first use}} for the diode was the {{demodulation}} of amplitude modulated (AM) radio broadcasts. The history of this discovery is treated in depth in the radio article. In summary, an AM signal consists of alternating positive and negative peaks of a radio <b>carrier</b> <b>wave,</b> whose amplitude or envelope {{is proportional to the}} original audio signal. The diode (originally a crystal diode) rectifies the AM radio frequency signal, leaving only the positive peaks of the <b>carrier</b> <b>wave.</b> The audio is then extracted from the rectified <b>carrier</b> <b>wave</b> using a simple filter and fed into an audio amplifier or transducer, which generates sound waves.|$|R
