40|$|The {{sensitivity}} of accelerometer {{can be changed}} with the amplitude of <b>carrier</b> <b>wave.</b> Based on the modeling of accelerometer, the mechanical characteristics are analyzed {{and the relationship between}} the elastic force and electrostatic force is obtained. The stable region of accelerometer reduces while the amplitude of <b>carrier</b> <b>wave</b> increases. The rolling test in 1 g gravitational field is carried out to calibrate the accelerometer with different <b>carrier</b> <b>waves.</b> The experiment results indicate that to keep the accelerometer working within the stable region, the amplitude of carrier should be selected from 1 V to 5 V. When the amplitude is less than 5 V, the {{sensitivity of}} the accelerometer will be improved with the increase of amplitude of <b>carrier</b> <b>wave,</b> while the linearity will be decreased. Once the voltage exceeds 5 V, the electrostatic force will equal to the elastic force, and this will lead the system into unstable state...|$|R
