5000|$|Demodulation is extracting the {{original}} information-bearing signal from a modulated <b>carrier</b> <b>wave.</b> A demodulator is an electronic circuit (or computer {{program in a}} software-defined radio) {{that is used to}} recover the information content from the modulated <b>carrier</b> <b>wave.</b> [...] There are many types of modulation so there are many types of demodulators. The signal output from a demodulator may represent sound (an analog audio signal), images (an analog video signal) or binary data (a digital signal).|$|R
